CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - PORT KEMBLA TO GOULBURN Various Roads
properties.otherAdvice:
A large number of oversize loads of varying dimensions and mass will depart Port Kembla for Grabben Gullen from Monday 6 May, weather permitting.

Most loads will be moved between 3am and 8am, up to six nights a week until November. This will involve up to three oversize loads under police escort leaving Port Kembla at 3am, travelling through Goulburn by 7.30am and arriving at Gullen Wind Farm by 8am.

Roads likely to be affected:
Tom Thumb Road, Springhill Road, Masters Road, F6 Freeway, Northern Distributor, Princes Highway, Mt Ousley Road, Picton Road, Hume Highway, Hume Street, Cowper Street, Clinton Street, Deacon Street, Fitzroy Street, Crookwell Road, Grange Road, Cullen Road and Range Road.

KINGS HWY CLOSED IN BOTH DIRECTIONS - Kings Hwy closed between Pooh Bear Corner and Top of Clyde Mountain
properties.otherAdvice:
The Highway is now closed until Thursday 5pm. Additionally, the highway will be closed for the following two weeks from 8am Tuesdays until 5pm Thursdays. These works will conclude by Thursday June 27. Closure times include Tuesday night, all day Wednesday and Wednesday night.

Light vehicles will be diverted at Braidwood and Batemans Bay and will detour via Nowra. This diversion will add about two and a half hours to the journey.

Heavy vehicles travelling from the south will need to travel via Cooma, using the Monaro Highway, Snowy Mountains Highway and the Princes Highway.

Heavy vehicles travelling from the north will need to travel via Wilton using the Hume Highway, Picton Road and the Princes Highway.

Araluen Road will have manned road closures in place during the Kings Highway work. Access will be restricted to local residents and proof of address will be needed to gain access.
